3
00:02:02,310 --> 00:02:04,080
Whoa...

4
00:02:13,110 --> 00:02:14,610
Alright!

5
00:02:17,030 --> 00:02:19,410
Aw, not again...

6
00:02:19,410 --> 00:02:20,620
Batter out!

7
00:02:20,620 --> 00:02:22,250
What're you doing?

8
00:02:22,250 --> 00:02:23,640
You suck!

9
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:32,630
This thing's heavy!

10
00:02:32,630 --> 00:02:36,340
Must be filled with booze, then!

11
00:02:47,310 --> 00:02:49,070
Ship off the starboard quarter!

12
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,610
It's flying a Jolly Roger!

13
00:02:51,610 --> 00:02:55,610
It's a pirate ship!
Enemy raid! Enemy raid!

14
00:03:19,390 --> 00:03:20,890
Koby!

15
00:03:21,140 --> 00:03:22,350
Y-Yes, ma'am?!

16
00:03:22,350 --> 00:03:25,890
On these seas, who's
the fairest of them all?

17
00:03:25,890 --> 00:03:30,610
Th-That'd obviously be the captain
of this ship, Lady Alvida!

18
00:03:36,650 --> 00:03:37,820
You got that right!

19
00:03:37,820 --> 00:03:39,820
Th-Thank you so much!

20
00:03:39,820 --> 00:03:42,450
Lady Alvida. Been awhile
since our last prey.

21
00:03:42,450 --> 00:03:43,540
It has.

22
00:03:44,040 --> 00:03:46,660
Alright! Start pounding that ship!

23
00:03:46,660 --> 00:03:48,890
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

24
00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:17,320
Men! Show them the terror
of the lady pirate, Iron Club Alvida!

25
00:04:27,660 --> 00:04:29,920
Koby! What are you doing?!

26
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:32,290
I-I'm not good at this sort of thing.

27
00:04:32,290 --> 00:04:33,540
Wha...?!

28
00:04:33,540 --> 00:04:36,210
Are you talking back to me?!

29
00:04:37,050 --> 00:04:39,970
P-Please, anything but the club!

30
00:04:40,930 --> 00:04:43,600
Then get your rear in gear!

31
00:05:04,450 --> 00:05:09,620
We won't take your lives,
but we will take all your valuables!

32
00:05:09,620 --> 00:05:14,420
Try to fight back, and you'll just
end up at the bottom of the ocean!

33
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:17,210
Hello...?

34
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:22,050
No one's in here, right?

35
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:24,800
Thank goodness... Hm?

36
00:05:26,890 --> 00:05:29,930
What a big barrel...

37
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:37,940
Hey, wimp!

38
00:05:37,940 --> 00:05:40,610
Hiding out again to
skip out on duties, huh?!

39
00:05:40,610 --> 00:05:44,820
N-No! I thought I should just roll
this barrel of booze over...

40
00:05:45,950 --> 00:05:47,950
Allow us to lighten the load!

41
00:05:47,950 --> 00:05:49,450
I was just getting thirsty...

42
00:05:49,450 --> 00:05:52,920
You can't! Lady Alvida will
kill us if she finds out!

43
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:55,670
Then you just gotta
keep your mouth shut!

44
00:05:55,670 --> 00:05:57,420
Right, Koby?

45
00:05:57,420 --> 00:06:00,880
Y-Yes! Absolutely!

46
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:02,170
It's damn heavy...

47
00:06:02,170 --> 00:06:03,340
I can't wait!

48
00:06:03,340 --> 00:06:05,470
I'll bust it right open!

49
00:06:15,060 --> 00:06:22,650
What a great nap!

50
00:06:25,950 --> 00:06:26,740
Huh?

51
00:06:30,870 --> 00:06:31,700
Who are you guys?

52
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:33,620
– Who the hell are you?!
– Who the hell are you?!

53
00:06:33,620 --> 00:06:35,630
He'll catch a cold napping there.

54
00:06:35,630 --> 00:06:37,460
– Because of you!
– Because of you!

55
00:06:39,130 --> 00:06:43,970
Bastard...! Who do you think you are,
messing with pirates, huh?!

56
00:06:44,260 --> 00:06:47,930
Man, I'm hungry! You got any food?

57
00:06:45,890 --> 00:06:47,930
Don't just ignore us!

58
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:50,430
You damn brat!

59
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:54,060
Die!

60
00:07:10,410 --> 00:07:12,500
What's the big idea?

61
00:07:12,830 --> 00:07:14,710
Wh-Who are you?!

62
00:07:14,710 --> 00:07:15,460
Me?

63
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:19,710
I'm Monkey D. Luffy.
Nice to meet you!

64
00:07:27,390 --> 00:07:29,640
What the...? What just happened?

65
00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:31,390
What's with them?

66
00:07:31,390 --> 00:07:33,020
H-Hurry! Get out of here!

67
00:07:33,020 --> 00:07:36,020
If they come back with
their friends, you'll be killed!

68
00:07:36,020 --> 00:07:38,020
But man, I sure am hungry!

69
00:07:38,020 --> 00:07:41,020
How can you be so carefree?!

70
00:07:41,020 --> 00:07:44,610
There are still lots more
of them up on deck!

71
00:07:44,610 --> 00:07:47,360
C'mon! This way!

72
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:48,820
H-H-Hey!

73
00:07:48,820 --> 00:07:51,780
Not this way!

74
00:07:56,960 --> 00:08:00,330
Food! Food! Food! Yes! Food!

75
00:08:00,330 --> 00:08:04,670
Actually, they might not
find us in here!

76
00:08:05,210 --> 00:08:08,630
Which should I choose?
This box? Oh, jackpot!

77
00:08:08,630 --> 00:08:10,390
These look tasty!

78
00:08:10,390 --> 00:08:13,010
M-My name is Koby.

79
00:08:13,010 --> 00:08:14,770
You're Luffy, right?

80
00:08:14,770 --> 00:08:17,640
That was incredible just now!
How did you do that?!

81
00:08:18,390 --> 00:08:19,600
These things are great!

82
00:08:21,230 --> 00:08:22,980
Is this a pirate ship?

83
00:08:22,980 --> 00:08:29,950
No, it's a passenger ship that's
being plundered by Lady Alvida.

84
00:08:29,950 --> 00:08:31,740
Makes no difference to me.

85
00:08:31,740 --> 00:08:33,950
Are there any small boats on board?

86
00:08:33,950 --> 00:08:36,500
I-I think so...

87
00:08:36,500 --> 00:08:38,960
My boat got swallowed
by this giant whirlpool!

88
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:42,590
You mean that whirlpool?!
It's a wonder you survived!

89
00:08:42,590 --> 00:08:46,050
Boy, was that a real surprise!

90
00:08:47,420 --> 00:08:50,430
Are you a pirate like them, or what?

91
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:50,430
Hm?

92
00:08:53,890 --> 00:08:56,970
It was on that fateful day...

93
00:08:57,480 --> 00:09:02,940
That day, I got in a boat on
the outskirts of town to go fishing...

94
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:14,740
but it turned out the boat was
actually headed for a pirate ship.

95
00:09:14,740 --> 00:09:16,620
It's been two years now.

96
00:09:16,620 --> 00:09:20,540
In exchange for my life, I was
forced to work as a cabin boy.

97
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:23,210
Man, you're a real idiot!

98
00:09:23,210 --> 00:09:25,250
You're brutally honest.

99
00:09:25,250 --> 00:09:26,500
Then just run away!

100
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:29,300
I-I can't! No way! No way!

101
00:09:29,300 --> 00:09:33,050
The thought of Lady Alvida finding me
makes me weak in the knees.

102
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:35,930
Oh, you're a wimp too?

103
00:09:35,930 --> 00:09:38,810
I really can't stand you!

104
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:43,150
Hey, now! Quit slacking off!

105
00:09:43,150 --> 00:09:46,020
Haul it all over before
the Marines get here!

106
00:09:46,980 --> 00:09:50,950
Any dawdlers get a taste of my iron club!

107
00:09:49,690 --> 00:09:50,950
What a haul!

108
00:09:56,870 --> 00:09:58,080
– Lady Alvida!
– Lady Alvida!

109
00:09:59,370 --> 00:10:00,040
– Bad news!
– Bad news!

110
00:10:00,410 --> 00:10:02,210
What is it?! You're ticking me off!

111
00:10:02,210 --> 00:10:03,620
A b-b-barrel!

112
00:10:03,620 --> 00:10:05,420
I-It's a monster!

113
00:10:05,420 --> 00:10:06,460
Huh?!

114
00:10:08,300 --> 00:10:10,420
Who are you calling a "monster"?!

115
00:10:17,930 --> 00:10:19,680
N-No...

116
00:10:19,680 --> 00:10:22,640
Some weird guy
popped out of a barrel...

117
00:10:22,640 --> 00:10:26,310
He might be a bounty hunter...

118
00:10:26,310 --> 00:10:27,940
What?!

119
00:10:28,980 --> 00:10:30,320
Yeah.

120
00:10:30,570 --> 00:10:31,820
That's right.

121
00:10:31,820 --> 00:10:36,320
If only I had your courage
to drift the seas in a barrel...

122
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:40,330
then I'd be able to accomplish
what I really want, too.

123
00:10:40,330 --> 00:10:44,580
Um... What compelled you
to set out to sea, Luffy?

124
00:10:44,580 --> 00:10:45,290
Huh?

125
00:10:45,790 --> 00:10:48,090
I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!

126
00:10:50,210 --> 00:10:52,340
K-K-King of the Pirates?!

127
00:10:52,340 --> 00:10:52,760
Yep.

128
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:53,840
Are you serious?!

129
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:54,470
I'm serious.

130
00:10:54,470 --> 00:10:57,260
Wait, you're a pirate, Luffy?!

131
00:10:57,260 --> 00:10:58,220
Yep.

132
00:10:58,220 --> 00:10:59,100
And your crew...?

133
00:10:59,100 --> 00:11:01,270
Don't have one. I'm looking, though.

134
00:11:05,850 --> 00:11:11,980
Th-Th-The King of the Pirates is the person who
obtains everything this world has to offer!

135
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:15,910
That means seeking ultimate
wealth, fame, and power—

136
00:11:15,910 --> 00:11:18,570
the One Piece,
the greatest hidden treasure!

137
00:11:18,570 --> 00:11:19,070
Yup!

138
00:11:19,070 --> 00:11:23,540
"Yup"?! Pirates all over the world
are after that treasure!

139
00:11:23,540 --> 00:11:24,580
Me too!

140
00:11:24,580 --> 00:11:28,420
No way! No way, no way, no way!
Absolutely no way!

141
00:11:28,420 --> 00:11:32,090
There's no way you can stand
at the summit of this Great Pirate Era!

142
00:11:32,090 --> 00:11:33,170
No way! No way!

143
00:11:35,510 --> 00:11:37,640
Why'd you hit me?

144
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:39,010
I felt like it.

145
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:42,640
I guess it's fine... I'm used to it now.

146
00:11:46,230 --> 00:11:48,100
It's not about whether I can...

147
00:11:48,100 --> 00:11:48,730
Huh?

148
00:11:48,730 --> 00:11:50,400
I'll do it because I wanna.

149
00:11:53,230 --> 00:11:56,740
I've decided to become
King of the Pirates...

150
00:11:56,740 --> 00:11:59,950
so if I die fighting for that,
then fine by me!

151
00:12:02,950 --> 00:12:07,160
Well, I'm stuffed!
Guess I'll go find a boat.

152
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:08,870
I wonder if they'll give me one.

153
00:12:08,870 --> 00:12:11,130
I hope they're generous.

154
00:12:12,040 --> 00:12:14,670
The thought never even
crossed my mind...

155
00:12:16,050 --> 00:12:18,260
Do you think I could do it too...

156
00:12:19,180 --> 00:12:20,890
if I'm prepared to die for it?

157
00:12:20,890 --> 00:12:21,720
Do what?

158
00:12:22,390 --> 00:12:23,510
Do you think...

159
00:12:24,010 --> 00:12:26,140
I could join the Marines?

160
00:12:27,100 --> 00:12:27,940
The Marines?

161
00:12:27,940 --> 00:12:31,730
Yes! Catching bad guys is my dream!

162
00:12:31,980 --> 00:12:34,190
It's been my dream
ever since I was little!

163
00:12:34,190 --> 00:12:35,940
Do you think I can do it?!

164
00:12:35,940 --> 00:12:37,070
How should I know?

165
00:12:37,070 --> 00:12:38,570
No! I'll do it!

166
00:12:38,570 --> 00:12:42,830
I either remain a chore boy
or break free and catch Lady Alvida!

167
00:12:42,830 --> 00:12:45,200
No, just Alvida!

168
00:12:52,040 --> 00:12:54,710
You wanna join up with this punk?!

169
00:12:54,710 --> 00:12:57,170
To catch who exactly?!

170
00:12:57,170 --> 00:12:59,930
Huh, Koby?!

171
00:13:13,900 --> 00:13:16,400
You don't look like Pirate Hunter Zoro.

172
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:18,190
Zoro?

173
00:13:18,190 --> 00:13:19,860
Koby!

174
00:13:20,110 --> 00:13:24,120
On these seas, who's
the fairest of them all?!

175
00:13:25,330 --> 00:13:27,290
O-Of course that would be–

176
00:13:27,910 --> 00:13:29,750
Who's this burly old lady?

177
00:13:36,210 --> 00:13:37,050
"Burly"?

178
00:13:37,050 --> 00:13:38,170
He didn't...

179
00:13:40,970 --> 00:13:44,140
You runt!

180
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:48,060
Let's go!

181
00:13:56,570 --> 00:13:57,690
Why, you...!

182
00:14:18,380 --> 00:14:21,800
It's not fair to attack from behind!

183
00:14:28,930 --> 00:14:32,980
It's also not fair to gang up on people!

184
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:43,280
Gotcha!

185
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:50,410
Gum-Gum...

186
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:55,250
Rocket!

187
00:14:56,170 --> 00:14:57,750
What?!

188
00:15:03,050 --> 00:15:06,260
L-Luffy... What are you?

189
00:15:06,260 --> 00:15:06,720
Me?

190
00:15:07,510 --> 00:15:09,180
I'm a rubber man!

191
00:15:09,810 --> 00:15:13,680
A rubber man...?
You can't be serious!

192
00:15:16,770 --> 00:15:19,440
You ate a devil fruit, didn't you?

193
00:15:20,190 --> 00:15:22,280
Yeah! The Gum-Gum Fruit!

194
00:15:22,530 --> 00:15:24,280
I see!

195
00:15:24,280 --> 00:15:29,490
I'd heard the rumors,
but I guess they really do exist!

196
00:15:29,830 --> 00:15:32,040
You're not too shabby, either.

197
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:33,410
You a bounty hunter?

198
00:15:33,790 --> 00:15:34,960
I'm a pirate!

199
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:36,710
A pirate?! Ha!

200
00:15:36,710 --> 00:15:37,790
All by yourself?!

201
00:15:37,790 --> 00:15:41,630
It's just me right now,
but I'm putting together a crew!

202
00:15:41,630 --> 00:15:44,470
I'm thinking... ten people sounds good!

203
00:15:44,470 --> 00:15:48,430
Then that means you and me
are enemies, huh?

204
00:15:48,430 --> 00:15:50,800
L-Luffy! Let's get out of here!

205
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:51,310
Why?

206
00:15:51,310 --> 00:15:53,470
You saw how powerful her club is!

207
00:15:53,470 --> 00:15:56,600
On these seas,
she's the number one...

208
00:15:59,150 --> 00:16:02,770
I've decided to become
King of the Pirates...

209
00:16:02,770 --> 00:16:06,070
so if I die fighting for that,
then fine by me!

210
00:16:09,070 --> 00:16:11,870
I'm the number one... what exactly?

211
00:16:11,870 --> 00:16:14,620
Th-Th-The...

212
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:21,290
The number one ugliest,
meanest old hag ever!

213
00:16:32,850 --> 00:16:35,140
Wh-What did you say?!

214
00:16:35,770 --> 00:16:38,140
I-I'm gonna join the Marines!

215
00:16:38,140 --> 00:16:41,150
And then I'll give you pirates hell!

216
00:16:41,150 --> 00:16:43,520
Do you even know
what you're saying?!

217
00:16:43,520 --> 00:16:47,150
I do! I'm gonna do what I wanna do!

218
00:16:47,150 --> 00:16:49,150
When I'm... When I'm a Marine...

219
00:16:49,150 --> 00:16:51,820
I'm gonna put you away for good!

220
00:16:51,820 --> 00:16:54,870
You damn pipsqueak!

221
00:16:54,870 --> 00:16:59,370
No regrets! No regrets!
I said it! I fought for my dream!

222
00:16:59,370 --> 00:17:00,460
Well said!

223
00:17:13,010 --> 00:17:14,350
That won't work!

224
00:17:14,350 --> 00:17:15,470
What?!

225
00:17:15,470 --> 00:17:17,100
I'm rubber, after all.

226
00:17:19,480 --> 00:17:23,730
Gum-Gum...

227
00:17:24,730 --> 00:17:30,150
Pistol!

228
00:17:48,260 --> 00:17:51,170
The sky is so blue...

229
00:18:02,850 --> 00:18:03,520
Hey!

230
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:04,400
– Yes?!
– Yes?!

231
00:18:04,400 --> 00:18:07,110
Give Koby a small boat!

232
00:18:07,110 --> 00:18:09,230
He's gonna join the Marines!

233
00:18:09,230 --> 00:18:10,690
So just let him go quietly.

234
00:18:11,450 --> 00:18:13,160
– R-Right!
– R-Right!

235
00:18:14,870 --> 00:18:16,200
Luffy...!

236
00:18:23,210 --> 00:18:25,330
It's the Marines!

237
00:18:25,330 --> 00:18:26,340
Oh!

238
00:18:26,670 --> 00:18:29,380
Perfect timing!
You should go see them!

239
00:18:29,380 --> 00:18:29,960
Huh?

240
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:31,340
But pirates have gotta run!

241
00:18:31,340 --> 00:18:32,340
Seriously?!

242
00:18:32,340 --> 00:18:36,050
Trying to join the Marines right now
will get me captured instead!

243
00:18:48,730 --> 00:18:50,940
We managed to get away, huh?

244
00:18:50,940 --> 00:18:53,280
Whew, that was fun!

245
00:18:54,280 --> 00:18:55,660
Um, Luffy....

246
00:18:55,660 --> 00:18:56,410
Yeah?

247
00:18:56,410 --> 00:19:01,200
If you're looking for the One Piece,
then you're off to the Grand Line, right?

248
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:01,790
Yup.

249
00:19:01,790 --> 00:19:04,920
That place is also called
the Pirate Graveyard, you know.

250
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:07,790
Yeah. So I'll need a strong crew.

251
00:19:08,290 --> 00:19:10,550
What about that Pirate Hunter guy?

252
00:19:10,550 --> 00:19:11,630
What's he like?

253
00:19:12,210 --> 00:19:13,720
You mean Zoro?

254
00:19:13,720 --> 00:19:17,390
I heard he's being held
prisoner at a Marine base.

255
00:19:17,390 --> 00:19:19,300
Oh? He's a weakling?

256
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:20,640
Not even!

257
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:24,430
He's like a terrifying demon!

258
00:19:25,850 --> 00:19:27,730
Why are you asking about him?

259
00:19:28,730 --> 00:19:31,690
If he's a good guy,
I thought he could join my crew!

260
00:19:33,030 --> 00:19:35,150
You're being reckless again!

261
00:19:35,150 --> 00:19:36,910
C'mon, he might be a good guy!

262
00:19:36,910 --> 00:19:39,160
He was caught
because he's a bad guy!

263
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:42,120
No! No way, no way, no way!
Absolutely no–

264
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:45,410
Why'd you hit me?

265
00:19:45,410 --> 00:19:46,620
